sendNotification

public java.lang.Object sendNotification(java.lang.String appId,
                                         java.lang.String recipients,
                                         java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> templateParameters,
                                         java.lang.String mediaItems)
Posts a notification to a list of recipients. At most 1000 recipients can be specified. You will need to pass in a template, which specifies the text in the notification, the buttons, and where the buttons link to.

Parameters:
recipients - A comma-separated list of recipients.
templateParameters - Parameters defining the template for the notification. This is a Map. Possible key values are:
  1. content (required) - Text content of the notification
  2. button0_surface (optional) - where button 0 should link to: "canvas" or "appProfile"
  3. button0_label (optional) - text label on button 0
  4. button1_surface (optional) - where button 1 should link to: "canvas" or "appProfile"
  5. button1_label (optional) - text label on button 1
mediaItems - A URI to a MySpace image, either a profile image or an album photo. External images are not allowed. At this time, only one media item is supported. (optional; pass null to not specify).
